The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 04 October is 78,026 (8,993 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 29 September, there were 2,504 new confirmed cases (288.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 September, there were 2,044 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 23% (460 extra cases).
